            <!--Example entries have been provided from MS I in the <handShift/>s below. Actual entries may vary.-->
            
            <div type="prose">
                <head type="title">151. "Sonnet to a Cloud" Witness</head>
                <p>151. &#x201C;Sonnet to a Cloud,&#x201D; <date when="1831-12">December 1831</date> to <date when="1832-01">January 1832</date>, 
                    MSS V, VIII. Printed PJR, 1:102; Works, 2:332.</p>
                
                <p>See no. 148 for dating. Follows no. 147 in MS V; in MS VIII, nos. 148&#x2013;50 and stanzas 5&#x2013;12 of no. 135 intervene 
                    between no. 147 and this poem. In MS VIII, entitled merely &#x201C;Sonnet.&#x201D;</p>
            </div>
            <!--Simple Verse. Delete this <div/> if not used.-->
            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title">Sonnet to a Cloud</head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>Thou little roamer of the northern blast</l>
                    <l>Mantling the brow of ruby fring&#x00E8;d morn<!--looks like fringed, no accent--></l>
                    <l>So swift so transient whither art thou borne</l>
                    <l>Hither and thither by the breezes cast</l>
                    <l>Hast shadowed sultry Araby or past</l>
                    <l>Lumed by the lightning on the gloomy storm<!--might be lightening?--></l>
                    <l>Or dimmed the lustre of the moon&#x00E8;s horn </l>
                    <l>Or swept oer mountain summit fleet and fast</l>
                    <l>Or darkened oer the bosom of the brine</l>
                    <l>Or wanton chased the summer breezes sigh <!--you had chased as fled, maybe I misread?--></l>
                    <l>And floated oer a <!--thirsty, salty, sultry?--> scorching clime<!--the word choice here doesn't look like thirsty to me, looks like it starts with an 's' and ends with 'ltry', but the second letter is peculiar--></l>
                    <l>Fading upon the clear and azure sky</l>
                    <l>Met<subst><del>hought</del><add>hinks</add></subst> I see thee like the wing of time</l>
                    <l>Melting away into eternity</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
            
            <div type="prose">
                <p>Textual note.&#x2014;As compared with the edited version in Works, <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskinâ€™s</persName> fair copy in MS V and his draft in MS VIII have all lines 
                    are flush left, without the editors' indentations; and first letters of lines and place names are capitalized. MS VIII version 
                    entirely unpunctuated; MS V unpunctuated, except for accents on &#x201C;fring&#x00E8;d&#x201D; (line 2) and &#x201C;moon&#x00E8;s&#x201D; (line 7). </p>
                
                <p>6, MS V, Works lightening] lightning MS VIII</p>
                <p>7, MS V moon&#x00E8;s] moons MS VIII; Works moon&#x00E8;&#x2019;s</p>
                <p>8, MS V mountain summit] mountains summit MS VIII; Works mountain-summit,</p>
                <p>10, MS V wanton fled] wanton [chased] fled MS VIII; Works wanton, fled</p> 
                <p>11, MS V a thirsty] a [sultry] thirsty MS VIII; Works a thirsty,</p>
                <p>13, MS V Methinks I see thee] Me[thought]thinks I see the MS VIII; Works &#x2014;Methinks I see thee</p>
            </div>
